1
00:00:00,840 --> 00:00:04,280
I was detained many times, and regarding the interrogation sessions

2
00:00:04,839 --> 00:00:09,560
They sometimes lasted long, sometimes they interrogated me, sometimes they didn’t

3
00:00:10,240 --> 00:00:12,080
Just to put psychological pressure on me

4
00:00:12,119 --> 00:00:14,679
My first interrogation was at Point 11

5
00:00:15,519 --> 00:00:19,960
I talked too much during the interrogation because of how unjustly they treated me

6
00:00:20,440 --> 00:00:24,760
I was innocent,I was just trying to earn a living, working as a taxi driver

7
00:00:25,199 --> 00:00:28,480
Because I talked so much, they interrogated me and took me to the judge

8
00:00:28,519 --> 00:00:31,280
Their system was that every week they brought us a blank sheet

9
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:33,920
We’d write our names, like Talal Mustafa al-Shuweimi

10
00:00:34,240 --> 00:00:37,119
Was he interrogated? If yes, he should write “yes”

11
00:00:37,520 --> 00:00:39,359
If not interrogated, he should write “no”

12
00:00:39,399 --> 00:00:41,240
And was he presented to the judge? “Yes” or “no”

13
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:45,560
And every time, I wrote “no,” blaming them for my case

14
00:00:46,399 --> 00:00:50,359
Since I had children, no means, and my house was rented in the beginning

15
00:00:51,640 --> 00:00:54,280
Sometimes they’d take me to the prison corridor

16
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,439
At Point 11

17
00:00:57,719 --> 00:01:01,479
They’d leave me for two or three hours, blindfolded

18
00:01:02,079 --> 00:01:03,079
Standing on my feet

19
00:01:03,719 --> 00:01:05,760
Or sitting on the ground

20
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:07,879
They wouldn’t speak to me or beat me

21
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:11,200
But I could hear the sounds of torture and beatings in the corridor

22
00:01:11,239 --> 00:01:15,760
They’d shout at the prisoners, Stand up, you dog! Turn around! Lift your foot! They had their own methods of torture

23
00:01:16,519 --> 00:01:23,640
But they didn’t beat me, they just kept me in the corridor blindfolded

24
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:26,120
Leaving me that way for two or three hours

25
00:01:26,159 --> 00:01:28,560
In the end, he’d say to me, Sheikh

26
00:01:28,599 --> 00:01:33,879
Go back to your group cell. I’d remove the blindfold inside and hand it to him through the window

27
00:01:33,959 --> 00:01:37,599
That happened about 10 times

28
00:01:38,519 --> 00:01:39,840
And the last time

29
00:01:41,959 --> 00:01:46,799
I told them I wanted to be interrogated because I was honestly afraid they’d put me in the corridor again

30
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:49,159
And one time

31
00:01:49,319 --> 00:01:50,560
I lost my patience

32
00:01:50,879 --> 00:01:53,120
I started crying and said, It’s only one death

33
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:55,200
A person only dies once

34
00:01:56,159 --> 00:01:59,920
I started crying and shouting, so they blindfolded me and took me away

35
00:02:00,719 --> 00:02:02,680
They took me to the interrogation room

36
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:04,439
And the interrogator

37
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:09,479
He died, may God have mercy on him

38
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:11,159
His name was Abu Abdul Rahman

39
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:14,639
He was from the Jaif area in Raqqa, from the Ghanem al-Zahir clan

40
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:17,719
He said to me, Talal al-Shuweimi

41
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:21,560
You

42
00:02:22,159 --> 00:02:23,599
Are you still doing amulet sorcery?

43
00:02:23,599 --> 00:02:30,719
Since I’m from the Marandiyya clan, and our ancestors were known for religion and for using drums

44
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:37,960
He said, Do you still make amulet spells and play the drums?

45
00:02:38,199 --> 00:02:40,560
And I knew him. I knew him well

46
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,240
I told him, I swear, Sheikh

47
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:48,039
I told him these words when you stop playing the <i>rababa</i> [string instrument]

48
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:52,280
He said to me, Are you the brother of Abdul Rahim Shuweimi?

49
00:02:52,719 --> 00:02:54,039
I said, Yes, I’m his brother

50
00:02:54,479 --> 00:02:55,960
I said, But, Sheikh

51
00:02:57,199 --> 00:02:58,639
At that time, my family was trying to use mediations for me

52
00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:04,360
My mother, an old woman, wherever she saw a clan sheikh or a member of ISIS

53
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:09,439
Any man with a long beard, she would go to him and say, My son has children, and so on

54
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:12,759
She would follow them around for her son, hoping they’d release me, and I had children

55
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:16,520
My children became my parents’ responsibility, and they had no power to help

56
00:03:18,159 --> 00:03:20,919
We argued about this topic

57
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:23,000
Then he said to me, You’re a filthy person

58
00:03:23,039 --> 00:03:26,879
I said, So now for you the Muslim is filthy, and Muslims deserve execution

59
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:30,039
It’s the rule of the strong over the weak, and there’s no power or strength

60
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:33,599
He said to me, God willing, you won’t leave this place

61
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:36,400
He brought in a man, and that man

62
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:40,080
Had a medium-sized passenger van

63
00:03:40,879 --> 00:03:44,360
His house was in the Kalta area in Raqqa’s countryside, and he used to transport female teachers

64
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:51,039
The group forced teachers to attend repentance courses. The point is, he used to drive those teachers

65
00:03:51,599 --> 00:03:55,280
The group accused him of smuggling people out of Raqqa

66
00:03:55,879 --> 00:03:57,759
They brought the man and blindfolded him

67
00:03:59,159 --> 00:04:01,039
That act was meant as punishment for me

68
00:04:01,479 --> 00:04:04,240
I felt it was a punishment for me, and while he was talking to me

69
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:06,120
He made me sit on a chair

70
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,120
While I was blindfolded

71
00:04:09,599 --> 00:04:15,719
I was only blindfolded and tied with plastic ties

72
00:04:15,759 --> 00:04:17,959
The kind used for bundling electric cables

73
00:04:19,879 --> 00:04:25,839
Then he brought the man and started beating him with a water hose called “Lakhdar Brahimi”

74
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,839
He disfigured the man’s body with the beating

75
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:29,519
The man cried intensely

76
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:35,759
I could hear the hose striking near me, and he kept beating him until he killed him

77
00:04:36,439 --> 00:04:40,240
Finally, I was so upset that I said, He’ll kill this man if he continues

78
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:45,759
I told him, I don’t want the interrogation anymore, just stop hitting him, because I realized he was doing it for my sake

79
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:48,959
He couldn’t hit me, not out of fear

80
00:04:49,439 --> 00:04:52,519
But because there was no proof against me, so he had no right to beat me

81
00:04:52,519 --> 00:04:56,639
And because Abu Yousuf the interrogator and Abu Suhaib the Tunisian were above him in rank

82
00:04:56,639 --> 00:05:01,759
Although Abu Suhaib the Tunisian was very strict religiously, he never allowed anyone to be beaten
